    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "at this stage in the process, the relay will either return the payload or not\r\n\r\nif they are not able to do so in a small number of seconds, something is probably up; the exact number could be measured if we had delivery metrics across all relays and say \"how long does it take for 99% of payloads to arrive?\"\r\n\r\nI would think in practice this number of actually much smaller than 3-4 seconds so we could be far more aggressive with the timeout\r\n\r\nthat being said, if the payload is not released it means a liveness failure for the chain so it is worth waiting for an excessive amount of time\r\n\r\n-- do the timeouts need to be synchronized? it may be nice but I don't really see the need to do so other than some unnecessary resource consumption by mev-boost while it is waiting the extra second",
