    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "ah great point! Leaving the timeout higher gives us more information, i.e. maybe the payload wasn't sent in 3s, but it was sent in say 3.5s as opposed to never being sent at all. And as you mention it doesn't matter to the validator what it is. \n\nIn terms of lowering the default, I think incentives take care of natural downward pressure on return time here and max \"safe\" wiggle room is good for unexpected circumstances.",
